article.headline: Denver 67, New Orleans 48
article.story: DENVER (AP) -- Center Yemi Nicholson scored 22 points and pulled down 16 rebounds as Denver beat New Orleans 67-48 Thursday night. Brett Seger added 15 points on 5-of-6 shooting and David Kummer added 14 points for Denver (7-6). Wayne Williams scored 22 points to lead New Orleans (3-9). New Orleans trailed 27-23 at the half, but battled back to tie the game at 33. A jumper and a dunk by Nicholson and a 3-pointer by Kummer gave the Pioneers a quick seven point lead. Seger and Kummer later hit several crucial 3-pointers as Denver built up its lead and then cruised to a 67-48 victory. Earlier, both teams New Orleans scored four consecutive points to take an early 6-2 lead, which was extended to 12-9 on a jumper by Williams.
